column5: Hey Mike, Did you get my e-mail? John
Don't think so John. I'm leaving for White River tonight (middle of the night).Resend it tonight or call me if you want.Cheers

Anyone going or have been to Beteau with Eddie North? We fished there the last 3 years but unfortunitly going to have to sit this year out.Going to try to put a trip together next year.Any reports would be great. Rob
Hey Rob, Hate to hear you are not going. Unfortunately I'm in the same boat. Cheers, John
6 of us heading into Windsor Jun 28 - Jul 05. I'll post/update after trip.
#@%*&, I had to sit this year out myself...my bud's are up at Eddie's right now and I am miserable! WW
I feel your pain, WW! John
I've looked at Eddie North's site, and it looks cool. I got the impression that it was mainly northern pike fishing. It is good walleye fishing too?
it's a river system.........when you find them you can load up quickly. Usually you get one while fishing for Northern, then you can work them over with jigs and plastics.
Tons of walleye and some big ones too.
Last year I got 30", 28 1/2", and 27 1/2"....all pb. So yes big walleyes!!!
Thanks. I'd like to go there someday. It looks incredible.
